cs.MS, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely category as the paper describes the development of a software tool for simulating self-assembly in the abstract Tile Assembly Model.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the aTAM involves the study of self-assembling structures and their properties, which can be analyzed using algorithms and data structures.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the aTAM is a model for studying the computational complexity of self-assembly.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a relevant category as the aTAM involves the study of geometric shapes and their assembly.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the aTAM can be used to model and study information networks and their self-assembly properties.
